ds. Isah further revealed that the team recovered 30 cows stolen from the village by the invaders. Subsequently, he explained that on August 7, “search parties led by the DPO and members of the community recovered additional seven corpses of the bandits who escaped with gunshot wounds at Barankada village, also in Batsari Local Government area.” Isah said that police recovered N22,300; 13 empty shells of live ammunition of 7.62mm as well as bunch of charms and keys from the bodies of the dead bandits. VANGUARD Katsina Police have reported they killed two suspected kidnappers, arrested six notorious bandits and recovered 130 rustled cows. The Katsina Police Command's Public Relations Officer, SP Gambo Isah, said this in a statement made available to newsmen in Katsina. “On Wednesday at about 22:00hrs, based on intelligence report, we gathered… May 29, 2020 In "News" No fewer than three suspected gunmen have been killed and two others arrested after a gun duel between security operatives and hoodlums in three communities in Batsari, Dutsin-ma and Safana Local Government Areas of Katsina State. July 31, 2020 In "News" The Police in Katsina State has confirmed 30 persons killed by bandits in Batsari Local Government Area of the state. February 15, 2020 In "News"